<DOC><DOCNO> ZF32-218-300 </DOCNO><DOCID>10 376 599</DOCID><JOURNAL>Newsbytes  Feb 20 1991* Full Text COPYRIGHT Newsbytes Inc. 1991.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>NTT to spin off mobile phones division. (Japanese telephonecompany reorganizes)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Miyazawa, Masayuki.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Company:   Nippon Telegraph and Telephone Corp. (Divestment).andO;Topic:     Telephone companiesReorganizationCellular radioTelecommunicationsJapan.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>NTT TO SPIN OFF MOBILE PHONES DIVISION 02/20/91 TOKYO, JAPAN, 1991 FEB 20(NB) -- NTT, the former state controlled telecommunications company of Japan,has announced plans to spin off its lucrative mobile phone operations,forming a separate company by 1992.andM;Plans call for the new company to become a parent firm itself in 1993, atwhich time it will create eight divisional companies, each of which willserve a region of Japan.andM;Why the spin off of the company? According to the Government, the creation ofa separate company will allow greater competition in the mobile telephonebusiness, eventually leading to a reduction in the cost of making mobilecalls in Japan.andM;(Masayuki Miyazawa/19910220)</TEXT></DOC>